  "prompt": "Do snakes really take revenge?",
  "response": "No, snakes do not take revenge. Snakes, like other animals, do not possess the cognitive ability to plan, strategize, or hold grudges. Their behaviors are primarily driven by instinct and survival needs, such as finding food, shelter, and avoiding predators. Actions that might be interpreted as aggressive or defensive are typically responses to immediate threats or stressful situations. Human concepts like revenge require advanced cognitive processes and emotions that snakes simply do not have.",
